,000 purchased. Delivery is ongoing.<ref>[http://www.asianmilitaryreview.com/CurrentIssue/dl.php?filename=201003140001071.pdf] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302011743/http://www.asianmilitaryreview.com/CurrentIssue/dl.php?filename=201003140001071.pdf|date=2 March 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:HK 21 LMG RIGHT SIDE.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Heckler & Koch HK21]] || Light machine gun || 5.56\u00d745mm NATO || {{Flagu|Germany}} ||<ref name=\"remtek\">{{cite news| title =The HK 21E Machine Gun: Mission Compatability &#91;sic&#93; Second to None|author=Gearinger, Stephen | url = http://www.remtek.com/arms/hk/mil/21/21.htm| accessdate = February 5, 2015|date=December 1998 |work=Small Arms Review }}</ref><ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|- \n| [[File:FN MAG white background.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[FN MAG|FN MAG-58]] || [[General purpose machine gun]] || [[7.62\u00d751mm NATO]] || {{Flagu|Belgium}} ||<ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Browning M1919a.png|centre|120px]] || [[M1919 Browning machine gun]] || General purpose machine gun || 7.62\u00d751mm NATO || {{Flagu|USA}} ||<ref name=\"sites.google.com\"/>\n|- \n| [[File:M60 machine gun.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[M60 machine gun|M60]] || General purpose machine gun || 7.62\u00d751mm NATO || {{Flagu|USA}} ||<ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|- \n| [[File:M2-Catlanit002.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[M2 Browning machine gun]] || [[Heavy machine gun]] || .50 BMG || {{Flagu|USA}} || Locally known as Type 93 machine gun (\u0e1b\u0e01.93). Use by infantry units and mobile vehicles and helicopters.<ref name=\"jones2009\"/>\n|-\n| [[File:Expomil 2005 01 TR-85M1 02 Mitraliera PKT.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[DShK|Type 54 HMG]] || Heavy machine gun || [[12.7\u00d7108mm]] || {{Flagu|China}} || Mounted on [[Type 69]] and small number of [[Cadillac Gage Commando|V-150]].<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/newrungsira/khet-thhar-ham-khea/xawuth-rabeid/punklhnaktxsuxakasyandshkmaahea