}} || M2 replaced by M3 variant.<ref>{{cite web |title=Direct fire support weapons land 40 phase 2 |url=http://www.defence.gov.au/dmo/lsd/land40/ |publisher=Defence Material Organisation |date=October 2010 |accessdate=24 April 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110410234803/http://www.defence.gov.au/dmo/lsd/land40/ |archivedate=10 April 2011 }}</ref><ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|- \n| [[File:Rcl106lat2.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[M40 recoilless rifle]] || Recoilless rifle ||   {{Flagu|US}} || Mounted on M151 utility vehicles.<ref name=\"UsaPublications2007\"/>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Vehicles===\n\n====Tanks and Armoured vehicles====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n!Photo\n!Model\n!style=\"width:13%;\"|Type \n!style=\"width:13%;\"|Origin  \n!Quantity\n!Notes\n|-\n! style=\"align: centre; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Tank]]s'''\n|-\n| [[File:BM Oplot, Kyiv 2018, 04.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[T-84|T-84 Oplot-M]] || [[Main Battle Tank]] || {{Flagu|Ukraine}} || 49<ref>{{cite news|title=5 things to know about Oplot|url=https://www.bbc.com/thai/thailand-43552888|first=BBC|last=Thai|date=28 March 2018|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>|| The government has approved 7.2 billion baht to purchase the first 49 T-84 Oplot main battle tanks to be assigned to the 2nd Cavalry Bn (Royal Guard at Fort Chakkraphongse, Prachinburi).<ref name=AR-20150414>{{cite news|title=Second batch of five T-84 Oplot-M Main Battle Tank for Thailand Army ready to be delivered| url=http://www.armyrecognition.com/april_2015_global_defense_security_news_uk/second_batch_of_five_t-84_oplot-m_main_battle_tank_for_thailand_army_ready_to_be_delivered.html|accessdate=17 July 2015|work=Army Recognition|date=14 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nonlen.com/news/19197/T-84-Oplot%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%96%E0%B8%96%E0%B8%B1%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%A2%E0%B8%B9%E0%B9%80%E0%B8%84%E0%B8%A3%E0%B8%99%E0%B8%AA%E0%B9%88%E0%B8%87%E0%B8%96%E0%B8%B6%E0%B8%87%E0%B9%84%E0%B8%97