0 Patton|M60A1/A3 Patton]] || Main battle tank ||  {{Flagu|US}}<br>{{Flagu|Israel}}|| 53<ref name=\"armyrecognition.com\">https://www.armyrecognition.com/thailand_uk/thai_thailand_army_land_ground_forces_military_equipment_armoured_vehicle_pictures_information_descr.html</ref><hr>125<ref name=\"armyrecognition.com\"/> ||  M60A1 RISE. Its have been in service since 1991  via FMS (Foreign Military Sales).<hr> M60A3 TTS. Fire Control Systems were upgraded by Israeli company Elbit Systems Land C4I LTD.<ref name=\"m60a3-type-85\" />\n|-\n| [[File:M-48A5E2 Ej\u00e9rcito Espa\u00f1ol.JPG|centre|120px]] || [[M48 Patton|M48A5PI Patton]] || Main battle tank || {{Flagu|Thailand}}<br>{{Flagu|US}}<br>{{Flagu|Israel}} ||105<ref name=\"armyrecognition.com\"/> || M48A5 equipped with the 105mm gun M68 of the [[M60 Patton]] tank by an Israeli-designed model.<ref name=\"AFV Database\">{{cite web|url=http://afvdb.50megs.com/usa/m48patton.html|title=90mm Gun Tank M48 Patton 48|accessdate=13 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150215112838/http://afvdb.50megs.com/usa/m48patton.html|archive-date=15 February 2015|url-status=live}}</ref>  M1 cupola also replaced by the Israeli Urdan model.\n|- \n| [[File:Irish Scorpion Tank.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[FV101 Scorpion]] || [[Light tank]] || {{Flagu|Thailand}}<br>{{Flagu|UK}} ||154<ref name=\"armyrecognition.com\"/>|| Modernized by Royal Thai Army Ordnance Department. Surveillance Target Acquisition and Weapon Sight from SELEX Galileo Ltd replacing its aging one. Replacing diesel-engine instead of gasoline-engine. New  tracks also were equipped.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thaifighterclub.org/webboard/17165/\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e17\u0e14\u0e2a\u0e2d\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e32\u0e07\u0e40\u0e17\u0e04\u0e19\u0e34\u0e04-\u0e23\u0e16\u0e16\u0e31\u0e07\u0e40\u0e1a\u0e32-21--Scorpion--\u0e08\u0e32\u0e01\u0e01\u0e32\u0e23\u0e0b\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e21\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e31\u0e1a\u0e1b\u0e23\u0e38\u0e07\u0e2a\u0e21\u0e23\u0e23\u0e16\u0e19\u0e30.html|t