vulcan.htm]- Military-today.com, 29 October 2019</ref><ref>http://www.imisystems.com/mediacenter/imi-systems-will-upgrade-royal-thai-army-m-163-vads/</ref>\n|-\n|  [[File:Type 59 57 mm AA MW front.JPG|120px]] || [[AZP S-60|Type 59]] || 57&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|China}}|| 24 in service. Chinese fragmentation round for anti-aircraft use, presumably similar to UOR-281/281U.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\" />\n|-\n| [[File:Bofors L60 IWM England.jpg|centre|120px]] ||[[40 mm Bofors|Bofors L60/70]] || 40&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|Sweden}} ||30 [[40 mm Bofors|L/60 (M1)]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\" />{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}<hr>16 [[40 mm Bofors|EL/70 LVS]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\" />{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}\n|-\n| [[File:Bofors-p004596.jpg|centre|120px]] ||[[40 mm Bofors|BAE Systems<br>EL/70 LVS]] || 40&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|UK}} || 70 [[40 mm Bofors|EL/70 LVS]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\" />{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}\n|-\n|  [[File:20mmVADS 2.JPG|centre|120px]] || [[M167 VADS]] || 20&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|US}} || 24 in service.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\" />\n|-\n|  [[File:Oerlikon GDF-006 35mm Twin Cannon Display at Chih Hang Air Force Base Apron 20130601a.jpg|120px]] || [[Oerlikon GDF]] || 35&nbsp;mm twin cannon towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|Switzerland}}|| 8 GDF-007 in service<ref name=\"thaimilitaryandasianregion_2015-11-06\">https://thaimilitaryandasianregion.wordpress.com/2015/11/06/rta-signed-for-skyguard-3-air-defense-systems/</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"align: centre; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Surface-to-air missiles]]'''\n|- \n| [[File:9K338 Igla-S (NATO-Code - SA-24 Grinch).jpg|centre|120px]] || [[9K38 Igla|9K38 Igla-S]] || [[Man-portable air-defence system]] ||   {{Flagu|Russia}} || Part of order placed in 2010.<ref name=SIPRI/><ref>[http://dtad.dti.or.th/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=220%3Aigla&catid=13%3Amissile-database&Itemid=2 \u0e08\u0e23\u0e27\u0e14\u0e15\u0e48\u0e2d\u0e2a\u0e39\u0e49\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e01\u0e32\u0e28\u0e22\u0e32\u0e19 SA-24 Grinch Igla-S <!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610231844/http://dtad.dti.or.th/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=220%3Aigla&catid=13%3Amissile-database&Itemid=2 |date=10 June 2015 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Soldier Mans Starstreak HVM High Velocity Missile System During Exercise Olympic Guardian for London 2012 MOD 45153958.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Starstreak (missile)|Starstreak]] || Surface-to-air missile || {{Flagu|UK}} || First ordered in 2012, additional ordered in 2015.<ref>[http://www.armyrecognition.com/november_2012_new_army_military_defence_industry/royal_thai_army_selects_thales_starstreak_air_defence_missile_system_1611121.html Royal Thai Army selects STARStreak] - Armyrecognition.com, 16 November 2012</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://defence-blog.com/news/royal-thai-army-places-additional-order-for-starstreak-air-defence-missile-systems.html|title=Royal Thai Army Places Additional Order for STARStreak Air Defence Missile Systems|publisher=defence-blog.com |date= 17 September 2015 |accessdate=4 January 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:MBDA MICA VL Lanceur terrestre Paris Air Show 2015.JPG|centre|120px]]|| [[MICA (missile)|VL MICA]] || Surface-to-air missile || {{Flagu|France}} || 1 enter service in 2019, receive two launchers and one command truck.<ref>http://thaidefense-news.blogspot.com/2019/03/vl-mica.html</ref><ref name=\"thai-army-unveils-vl-mica-air-defence-system\">https://www.shephardmedia.com/news/landwarfareintl/thai-army-unveils-vl-mica-air-defence-system/</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===Radar systems===\n\n====Air search radars, Artillery-locating radars====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width: