ightglobal.com/asset/21905/waf/|archive-date=6 February 2018|accessdate=18 May 2018|df=dmy-all}}</ref>|| Will replace by [[Boeing AH-6]]. Four were ordered in 1988 and another four were ordered in 2005.<ref name=\"Trade Registers\">{{cite web|url=http://armstrade.sipri.org/armstrade/page/trade_register.php |title=Trade Registers |publisher=Armstrade.sipri.org |date= |accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref><ref name=\"AH-1 Cobra retirement program at Fort Drum ends; final four helicopters head to Thailand\">{{cite web|url=http://www.army.mil/article/46906 |title=AH-1 Cobra retirement|author=Paul Steven Ghiringhelli |publisher=United States Army |date=21 October 2010|accessdate=4 August 2014}}</ref> One was lost in 2001 crash. Three in storage for spare parts.\n|-\n| [[File:SAS 2010 Boeing AH-6.JPG|centre|120px]] || [[Boeing AH-6]] || [[Attack helicopter|Light Attack helicopter]] || {{Flagu|US}} || 0+(8)<ref>{{Cite web|title=DOS clears US$400 mn Thai attack chopper deal|url=https://asiatimes.com/2019/09/article/us-oks-400-mn-thai-attack-helicopter-purchase/|website=www.asiatimes.com|first=thairath|last=online|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=3 October 2019}}</ref> || 8 on order.<ref>{{Cite web|title=DOS clears US$400 mn Thai attack chopper deal|url=https://www.thairath.co.th/news/politic/1669056|website=www.thairath.co.th|first=DM|last=CHAN|date=26 September 2019|accessdate=1 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Airbus AS550 Fennec.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Eurocopter Fennec|Eurocopter Fennec AS550 C3]] ||Light Attack helicopter || {{Flagu|France}} ||8<ref name=\" WAF 2018\" />||\n|-\n| [[File:Sikorsky UH-60 Blackhawk of the Royal Thai Army at Khon Kaen (8876686169) (2).jpg|centre|120px]] || [[UH-60 Black Hawk|Sikorsky UH-60L/M Blackhawk]] || [[Utility helicopter]] ||{{Flagu|US}} ||12<ref name=\" WAF 2019\">https://dl.cypc.fr/Documents/Aviation/General/World%20Air%20Forces%202019.pdf</ref>||UH-60Ls.<ref>[http://www.dsca.mil/PressReleases/36-b/2009/Thailand_09-49.pdf] {{webarch