0e31\u0e48\u0e07\u0e0b\u0e37\u0e49\u0e2d VT-4 \u0e2d\u0e35\u0e01 11 \u0e04\u0e31\u0e19/RTA Buy Another 11 VT-4s (UPDATE II)|first=|last=Administrator|date=|website=thaiarmedforce.com|access-date=2019-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160516202146/http://www.thaiarmedforce.com/taf-military-news/53-rta-news/814-rta-signed-for-vt-4-mbt.html|archive-date=2016-05-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> The RTA has signed an agreement with China to procure the VT-4 main battle tank (MBT), features an initial 28 units, with deliveries expected to commence before the end of 2016 and conclude within two years. The deal is thought to be valued at about US$150 million. If the first batch of deliveries is successful, sources indicated the RTA would look to procure additional VT-4s as it seeks to meet a long-standing requirement for up to 150 MBTs.<ref name=\"IHS Jane's 360\"/>\n* '''M1126 Infantry Carrier Vehicle''' - In May 2019 [[Royal Thai Army]] ordered 37 refurbished [[M1126 Infantry Carrier Vehicle]]s from U.S. Army and will also receive 23 more M1126 vehicles.<ref>https://theworldnews.net/th-news/army-seals-deal-to-buy-us-armour</ref>\n\n===Indigenous===\n* [[Black Widow Spider armored car|Black Widow Spider]]\n* [[Phantom 380-X armored car|Phantom 380-X]]\n* [[DTI-2]]/[[DTI-2G]]\n* [[UAV RD01]]\n* [[Black Kite UAV]]\n* [[T-eagle Eye III]]\n\n==Historical equipment==\n{|border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:80%;\"\n|-style=\"background:#ccc;\"\n|'''Name'''||'''Country of Origin'''||'''Type'''||'''Service'''||'''Quantity'''||'''Note'''\n|-style=\"background:#cddae7;\"\n|colspan=\"6\"|'''Infantry weapons'''\n|-\n| [[Steyr-Mannlicher M1888]] || {{flagcountry|Austria-Hungary}} || [[Bolt-action]] [[rifle]] || 1890\u2013? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Siamese Mauser style rifle|Type 46 Siamese Mauser]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.weekendhobby.com/gun/webboard/question.asp?page=7&ID=3810 |title=\u0e04\u0e33\u0e15\u0e2d\u0e1a\u0e17\u0e35\u0e48 182  |publisher=Weekendhobby.c