ado M113 (Ej\u00e9rcito brasile\u00f1o) en.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[M113 armored personnel carrier|M113A1/A2/A3]] ||  Armoured personnel carrier || {{Flagu|US}} ||426 <ref name=\"nimda-m113\">https://aagth1.blogspot.com/2018/01/nimda-m113.html</ref>||426 of M113 family are armoured personnel carriers, command variant in M577A3 variant, ARV in M113A3 variant, ambulances in M113A3 and mortar carrier in M125 and M106 variants.<ref name=\"nimda-m113\"/>\n|- \n| [[File:Thai Type 85 APCs during 2010 Thai political protests 2.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Type 85 AFV|Type 85]] || Armoured personnel carrier || {{Flagu|China}} ||396<ref name=srrphawuth></ref> ||Variants include: APC, ACV,SPM 120mm, SPM 81mm, SPRL. Type 85 is being upgraded APC Modification kits, Spare Parts, Special Purpose Equipment & Tooling for Overhaul and Upgrade and Technical Service.<ref name=\"m60a3-type-85\">https://aagth1.blogspot.com/2019/02/m60a3-type-85.html</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Chaiseri First Win.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[First Win|First Win 4x4]] ||   [[Infantry mobility vehicle]] || {{Flagu|Thailand}} ||21<ref>https://www.janes.com/article/65260/thailand-s-first-win-for-malaysia-indodef16-d3</ref>|| Mine-protected vehicle.\n|- \n| [[File:Reva APC.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Reva APC|REVA 4x4 MKII]] || Infantry mobility vehicle || {{Flagu|South Africa}} ||87<ref>http://defense-studies.blogspot.com/2009/12/thailands-armed-forces-modernisation.html</ref>|| Mine-protected vehicle.\n|- \n| [[File:1HumveeatRatchaprarop.jpg|centre|120px]] || [[Humvee]] || [[Armored car (military)|Light Armored Car]]/[[Light utility vehicle]] || {{Flagu|US}} ||Unknown|| RTA use M998, M1038A1, M1097A1, M1037, M1042, M1025, M1026A1, M966, M997, M997A2.\n|}\n\n====Support vehicles and support equipments====\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:90%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:9%;\"| Photo\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Model\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Type\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Origin\n! Notes\n|-\n! style=\"align: centre; background: lavender