2 Duster]] || 40&nbsp;mm  [[self-propelled anti-aircraft gun]] ||  {{Flagu|US}} || 18 in service.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\">https://sites.google.com/site/faminacgm/yuththopkrn-thi-praca-kar-nipa/xawuth-pra-cak/xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas</ref>\n|- \n| [[File:M163 VADS.JPEG|centre|120px]] || [[M163 VADS]] || 20&nbsp;mm self-propelled anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|US}}<br>{{Flagu|Israel}} || 24 in service. Currently undergoing upgrade by IMI.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref><ref>[http://www.military-today.com/artillery/m163_vulcan.htm]- Military-today.com, 29 October 2019 </ref><ref>http://www.imisystems.com/mediacenter/imi-systems-will-upgrade-royal-thai-army-m-163-vads/</ref>\n|-\n|  [[File:Type 59 57 mm AA MW front.JPG|120px]] || [[AZP S-60|Type 59]] || 57&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|China}}|| 24 in service. Chinese fragmentation round for anti-aircraft use, presumably similar to UOR-281/281U.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref>\n|-\n| [[File:Bofors L60 IWM England.jpg|centre|120px]] ||[[40 mm Bofors|Bofors L60/70]] || 40&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|Sweden}} ||30 [[40 mm Bofors|L/60 (M1)]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref>{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}<hr>16 [[40 mm Bofors|EL/70 LVS]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref>{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}\n|-\n| [[File:Bofors-p004596.jpg|centre|120px]] ||[[40 mm Bofors|BAE Systems<br>EL/70 LVS]] || 40&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|UK}} || 70 [[40 mm Bofors|EL/70 LVS]] in service<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref>{{sfn|Military Balance 2016|pp=293-294}}\n|-\n|  [[File:20mmVADS 2.JPG|centre|120px]] || [[M167 VADS]] || 20&nbsp;mm towed anti-aircraft gun ||  {{Flagu|US}} || 24 in service.<ref name=\"xawuth-praca-hnwy-pxngkan-phay-thang-xakas\"></ref>\n|-\n