er S-300C]] || [[Military helicopter#Observation helicopters|Observation]]/[[Military helicopter#Training helicopters|Trainer helicopter]] ||  {{Flagu|US}} ||45<ref name=\" WAF 2018\"></ref>|| For observation and training \n|-\n| [[File:G-LADD-Enstrom480.jpg|centre|120px]] ||  [[Enstrom 480]]B || Trainer helicopter ||  {{Flagu|US}} ||16<ref name=\" WAF 2018\"></ref>|| For training \n|-\n| [[File:G-OCAF Robinson R44 Helicopter (47122402961).jpg|centre|120px]] ||  [[Robinson R44]]|| Trainer helicopter ||  {{Flagu|US}} ||1<ref name=\" WAF 2018\"></ref>|| For training \n|-\n! style=\"align: centre; background: lavender;\" colspan=\"7\" | '''[[Fixed-wing aircraft]]'''\n|-\n| [[File:Royal Thai Army C-295W (31242247700).jpg|120px]] ||[[EADS CASA C-295|CASA C-295W]] || [[Cargo aircraft|Transport aircraft]] || {{Flagu|Spain}} ||1<ref name=\" WAF 2018\"></ref>||The RTA ordered one C-295W.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://militaryaircraft-airbusds.com/Portals/0/Images/Aircraft/OrdersAndDeliveries/AMOrdersDeliveries.pdf|publisher=Airbus Defence & Space|title=Orders, Deliveries, In Operation Military aircraft by Country - Worldwide|accessdate=18 June 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151120091009/http://www.militaryaircraft-airbusds.com/Portals/0/Images/Aircraft/OrdersAndDeliveries/AMOrdersDeliveries.pdf|archive-date=20 November 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[File:CASA C-212-300 Aviocar, Thailand - Army AN1641411.jpg|centre|120px]]|| [[C-212 Aviocar|CASA C-212-300 Aviocar]] || transport aircraft ||  {{Flagu|Spain}} ||2<ref name=\" WAF 2018\"></ref> || Serial numbers 446 and 447 based with the VIP squadron at [[Don Mueang Airport]].  \n|-\n| [[File:Embraer ERJ-135LR of the Royal Thai Army at Khon Kaen-KKC.jpg|centre|120px]] ||[[Embraer ERJ 145 family|Embraer ERJ-135LR]] || [[Air transports of heads of state and government|VIP transport aircraft]] || {{Flagu|Brazil}} ||2 ||Both aircraft delivered (serial numbers 1084/HS-AMP and 1124)<ref>[http://www.embraer.com/englis