ors L/24 Model 1934]] || {{SWE}} || 150&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1936\u2013? || 8 ||\n|-\n| [[Bofors L/22 Model 1936]] || {{SWE}} || 105&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1938\u2013? || 20 ||\n|-\n| [[10.5 cm kanon m/34|Bofors L/42 Model 1934]] || {{SWE}} || 105&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1935\u2013? || 4 ||\n|-\n| [[Bofors L/40 Model 1934]] || {{SWE}} || 75&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1938\u2013? || 52 ||\n|-\n| [[Type 63 Field gun]] || {{flagicon|Thailand|1855}} [[Rattanakosin Kingdom|Siam]] || 75&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1920\u2013? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Krupp 7.5 cm Model 1903|Krupp L/30 Model 1903]] || {{flag|German Empire}} || 75&nbsp;mm [[field gun]] || 1908\u2013? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Bofors L/20 Model 1929]] || {{SWE}} || 75&nbsp;mm [[mountain gun]] || 1934\u2013? || 8 ||\n|-\n| [[Type 49 Krupp]] || {{flag|German Empire}} || 50&nbsp;mm [[mountain gun]] || 1906\u20131922 || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Type 77 Bofors Model 1934]] || {{SWE}} || 47&nbsp;mm/75&nbsp;mm [[dual purpose gun]] || 1934\u2013? || 32 ||\n|-\n| [[M116 howitzer|M1A1]] || {{USA}} || 75&nbsp;mm [[pack howitzer]] || 1954\u2013? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Type 76 Vicker Armstrong]] || {{UK}} || 40&nbsp;mm [[self-propelled anti-aircraft gun]] || 1933\u2013? || 26 ||\n|-\n| [[Bofors L/50 Model 1930]] || {{SWE}} || 75&nbsp;mm [[anti-aircraft gun]] || 1934\u2013? || 18 || 8 ordered in 1934 and 10 ordered in 1937.\n|-\n| [[37 mm automatic air defense gun M1939 (61-K)|Type 74]] || {{CHN}} || 37&nbsp;mm [[anti-aircraft gun]] || ? \u2013? || 52 ||\n|- \n| [[M45 Quadmount|M55]] ||  {{USA}} ||  4 x [[M2HB]] machine guns || ? \u2013? ||  ||\n|-\n| [[M16 MGMC]] ||  {{USA}} ||  4 x M2HB machine guns  || ? \u2013? ||  || \n|-\n| [[Type 97 90 mm Infantry Mortar|Type 97 90&nbsp;mm]] || {{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}} || [[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || 1941\u2013? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Type 97 81 mm infantry mortar|Type 97 81&nbsp;mm]] || {{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}} || [[Mortar (weapon)|Mortar]] || ? || ? ||\n|-\n| [[Type 11 70 mm Infantry Mortar|Type 11 70&